#3001
@@WCedar Square@@N~
The western terminus of @@WMidgaard@@N's uppermost avenue opens into a broad civic pocket paved with river-smoothed flagstone. Cedar timbers brace the shopfronts to either side, their grain darkened by generations of lamp oil and weather, and a squat stone water trough stands where porters pause to refill their skins. The air here carries sawdust and the faint resin scent of the cedar beams that gave this square its name, mingling with distant hymns from somewhere deeper in the city. Underfoot, faded @@cpaving sigils@@N mark an old Lantern Reform survey line that the watch still uses as a reference when chalking patrol routes.
