This stretch of the upper avenue is lined with narrow-fronted silversmiths and assay offices whose display cases catch the @@ylantern@@N light in pale flashes. The walkway is wide enough for two handcarts abreast, and the cobbles underfoot have been worn smooth by decades of trade traffic between the cedar quarter to the west and the dyers' row to the east. A tin notice plate nailed to a lintel post lists the current tariff schedule in cramped municipal script.
