A ceremonial arch of dark basalt stands at the center of this junction, its keystone inlaid with bands of violet lacquer that gleam under the concentrated lamplight the city maintains here day and night. @@cWarding sigils@@N etched into the arch's inner face record the terms of the @@pViolet Compact@@N, the old civic agreement that formalized registry-based oversight of all occult passages beneath @@WMidgaard@@N. Cold air seeps steadily upward from the stairway that descends into the @@dGloamvault of Kel'Shadra@@N, carrying a mineral chill that makes the lantern flames gutter. City stewards have reinforced this threshold with extra lamps, posted oath plaques, and a standing guard detail so that no traveler passes through unaware. A brass plate bolted to the arch's western pillar lists the civic offices responsible for access control, and a smaller notice reminds visitors that all registry-bound artefacts must be declared before descent.
