The western gate-ward junction of the third ring opens where Cedar Square meets the @@yRoc Road@@N, the overland route that leads west toward Kiess and the ruins of fallen Evermeet. A stone milestone set into the pavement marks the formal boundary of @@WMidgaard@@N's civic jurisdiction, its face inscribed with distances to the nearest waystations along the western corridor. Gate wardens maintain a checkpoint here, their kiosk decorated with posted travel advisories and a map-board showing known hazards on the Roc Road. The architecture transitions at this point from city stone to the heavier gatehouse construction of the Fortification Era, and the foot traffic includes a visible proportion of armed travelers preparing for departure. A carved city-seal pillar stands beside the western exit, its base polished smooth by the hands of those who touch it for luck before setting out.
