@@WGranite Arcade@@N~
The granite arcade on this tier serves a more practical function than the notarial colonnade above, housing a levee office where river cargo is inspected and taxed before entering the city's commercial stream. The pillars here are thicker and less refined, their surfaces scarred by decades of cargo being dragged past them, and the floor is stained with the spilled contents of countless broken crates. A retired sea captain operates a small chandlery from one of the arcade bays, selling nautical supplies and boats to anyone willing to navigate the local waterways.
