@@WThe Temple of the Resounding Heart@@N~
The largest religious structure in @@WMidgaard@@N occupies this prominent intersection, its vaulted stone interior open to visitors at all hours. Polished granite columns support a high ceiling from which iron @@ycandelabra@@N hang on long chains, their flames casting a steady golden light across the mosaic floor depicting the city's founding compact. The temple serves multiple civic functions beyond worship: it houses the charitable healing clinic, maintains the memorial rolls of the dead, and provides sanctuary to those in need of protection under temple law. Along the western wall, a carved panel lists the names of all known dead from the city's major conflicts, updated annually by the @@WTemple Memorist@@N in a public ceremony. A narrow stair descends to the donation halls below, while another ascends toward the higher sanctuary. The air carries the scent of beeswax candles and dried rosemary, and the murmur of quiet prayer provides a constant background that absorbs the noise from the busy streets outside.
