@@WBronze Colonnade@@N~
The bronze pillars continue their march along the northern edge of this lower corridor section, though here the patina has deepened to a near-black green that contrasts sharply with the pale limestone buildings behind them. A tattered canvas banner strung between two pillars advertises a seasonal market fair that ended weeks ago, its rope ties too high for any casual passer-by to reach and remove. The street narrows slightly where a building's upper floor extends over the walkway on corbeled supports, creating a brief stretch of covered passage.
