@@WSunward Way@@N~
The lower tier of Sunward Way sits in the permanent shadow of the taller buildings on the corridor above, a irony not lost on the locals who have taken to calling this stretch the Dark Half with characteristic civic humor. The @@ylanterns@@N here burn throughout the day as a result, their fuel costs subsidized by a Standardization-era ordinance that mandates minimum illumination levels on all named streets regardless of natural light conditions. A drainage grate in the center of the street channels runoff from the upper tiers, its iron bars clogged with debris that the ward janitor clears on a weekly schedule.
