@@WMarble Ring@@N~
The Marble Ring's compass medallion is repeated here in miniature — a smaller version set into the wall rather than the floor, installed during a later administration that wanted to extend the wayfinding system to all tiers of the grid. The execution is less impressive than the original, using painted ceramic rather than true marble, but the directional information is accurate and regularly maintained. The surrounding buildings house a mix of residential tenants and small workshop operations, their facades distinguished by the hand-painted trade signs that line the upper stories.
