@@WSaffron Walk@@N~
The yellowish limestone of the upper Saffron Walk gives way here to a darker, weathered variant quarried from deeper deposits — the same stone but aged differently by exposure and the dampness that accumulates on the lower tiers. A public water pipe juts from the wall at waist height, its bronze tap worn smooth by constant use and dripping steadily into a shallow stone basin below. Locals gather here in the mornings to fill jugs and exchange the day's gossip before heading to their workshops and market stalls.
