Lower Ember Court has developed its own identity distinct from the demolished-smithy origin of its upper namesake. Here the open space serves as a small staging area for delivery carts, its cobblestones worn into shallow ruts by years of wheel traffic following the same narrow route between the market streets and the southern gate approaches. A stone hitching post at the corner bears rope marks from generations of tethered draft animals, and a battered tin water trough beside it is kept filled by the ward's civic maintenance crew.
