@@WIvory Passage@@N~
The limestone walls of the lower Ivory Passage bear dark water stains from a persistent seepage problem that the civic engineers have addressed with a series of shallow drainage channels cut into the base of the walls. The channels work well enough to keep the passage walkable, but the constant trickle of water gives the air a damp coolness that contrasts with the warmer streets on either side. An iron grate set into the floor at the passage's midpoint drains into the city's underground cistern system, its opening covered by a locked hatch that only the Waterworks Guild holds keys for.
