@@WMoonlit Approach@@N~
The lower Moonlit Approach shares the lamp-line gap of its upper tier, though here the darkness is deeper owing to the taller buildings that block ambient light from neighboring streets. Residents have adapted more extensively than on the upper stretch — candle-lanterns hang from hooks above nearly every door, and a communal oil lamp mounted on a repurposed hitching post at the corridor's midpoint provides a welcome pool of light. The effect is warmer and more intimate than the uniform civic illumination of the surrounding streets, and some residents reportedly resist proposals to extend the official lamp-line, preferring the neighborhood's distinctive character.
